===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/zɛi̯n/|lang=nl}}
* {{audio|Nl-zijn.ogg|audio}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|dum|nl}} {{term|sijn|lang=dum}}, from {{etyl|odt|nl}} {{term|sin|sīn|lang=odt}}. The infinitive {{term||zijn|lang=nl}} along with the words {{term|is|lang=nl}} and {{term|zij|lang=nl}} (present indicative and subjunctive) derive ultimately from {{etyl|ine-pro|nl}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*h₁es-||to be}}, which had no separate infinitive in Germanic. The modern infinitive was probably back-formed in late Old Dutch from the first-person plural subjunctive {{term||sīn|we be|lang=odt}}, since this form had become identical to the infinitive in other verbs during the late Old Dutch period. Compare also German {{term|sein|lang=de}}, Low German {{term|sön|lang=nds}}.

The original infinitive survives in {{term|wezen|lang=nl}}, from {{etyl|dum|nl}} {{term|wesen|lang=dum}}, from {{etyl|odt|nl}} {{term|wesan|lang=odt}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|nl}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*wesaną}}, from {{term/t|ine-pro|*h₂wes-||to reside}}. All the forms with initial ''w-'' (imperative and past tense) derive from this root.

Finally, the forms {{term|ben|lang=nl}} and {{term|bent|lang=nl}} derive from {{etyl|gem-pro|nl}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*beuną||to be, to become}}, from {{term/t|ine-pro|*bʰuH-||to become}}, which survives only as relic forms in the West Germanic languages and not at all in the others. Its infinitive and non-singular forms are only attested in (Old) English.

====Verb====
{{nl-verb}}

# {{context|intransitive|lang=nl}} To [[be]], to [[exist]].
#: {{usex|'''Zijn''' of niet '''zijn''', dat is de vraag.|t=To '''be''' or not to '''be''', that is the question.|lang=nl}}
#: {{usex|'''Was''' je er afgelopen zaterdag ook?|t='''Were''' you there too last Saturday?|lang=nl}}
# {{context|transitive|copular|lang=nl}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to connect a noun to an adjective that describes it.}}
#: {{usex|De bal '''is''' rond.|t=The ball '''is''' round.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|transitive|auxiliary|lang=nl}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the [[perfect tense]] of the [[active voice]] of some verbs, together with a [[past participle]].<br/>'''Note:''' The perfect tense of most other verbs is formed using [[hebben]].}}
#: {{usex|Hij '''is''' hier geweest.|t=He '''has''' been here.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|transitive|auxiliary|lang=nl}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the [[perfect tense]] of the [[passive voice]], together with a [[past participle]].<br/>'''Note:''' The [[imperfect tense]] passive is formed using [[worden]].}}
#: {{usex|Ze '''waren''' gered.|t=They '''had been''' saved.|lang=nl}}
#: {{usex|De muur '''is''' geschilderd.|t=The wall '''has been''' painted.|lang=nl}}
#: {{usex|De muur zal '''zijn''' geschilderd.|t=The wall will '''have been''' painted.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|transitive|auxiliary|lang=nl}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the continuous forms of various tenses, together with '''[[aan het]]'''.}}
#: {{usex|De man '''was''' aan het lopen.|t=The man '''was''' walking.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=nl}} To [[go]], to go on a [[trip]] and return.
#: {{usex|Ik '''ben''' even naar de dokter.|t=I '''am going''' to the doctor for a while.|lang=nl}}
#: {{usex|Ik ben vandaag naar het strand '''geweest.'''|t=I've '''been''' to the beach today.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|intransitive|impersonal|lang=nl}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to indicate weather, temperature or some other general condition.}}
#: {{usex|Het '''is''' erg warm vandaag.|t=It '''is''' very warm today.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|transitive|copular|mathematics|lang=nl}} To [[equal]]; {{non-gloss definition|used to indicate that the values on either side of an equation are the same.}}
#: {{usex|Drie keer vijf '''is''' vijftien.|t=Three times five '''equals''' fifteen.|lang=nl}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=nl}} To have the next [[turn]] in a [[game]].
#: {{usex|Jij '''bent''' nu.|t=It '''is your turn''' now.|lang=nl}}

